stateDiagram-v2
    classDef okState fill:#dce7f2,stroke:#2e5f8a,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#1f2933
    classDef offState fill:#e8eaed,stroke:#6b7480,color:#1f2933
    classDef declState fill:#f2f4f7,stroke:#52606d,stroke-dasharray:4 3,color:#1f2933

    state "PENDING" as PEN
    state "COMPLETED" as DONE
    state "FAILED" as FAIL
    state "EXPIRED" as EXP
    state "CANCELLED" as CAN

    [*] --> PEN : create session on a VERIFICATION flow<br/>(expires_at = now + 30 min)

    PEN --> PROG : first step result submitted<br/>(session.start)

    state "IN_PROGRESS — one result per flow step" as PROG {
        state "PENDING" as SP
        state "IN_PROGRESS" as SI
        state "COMPLETED" as SC
        state "FAILED" as SF
        state "PENDING_REVIEW" as SR
        state "SKIPPED" as SS
        [*] --> SP
        SP --> SI : handler executes
        SI --> SC : handler passed<br/>(confidence + result data)
        SI --> SF : handler failed or<br/>client-reported error
        SI --> SR : handler defers<br/>(e.g. VIDEO_INTERVIEW)
        SP --> SS : optional step skipped
        SR --> SC : admin approves
        SR --> SF : admin rejects
    }

    PROG --> DONE : all flow steps COMPLETED or SKIPPED<br/>(auto-complete) — user marked<br/>identity-verified at computed level
    PROG --> FAIL : any step FAILED

    PEN --> EXP : submission after expires_at
    PROG --> EXP : submission after expires_at

    PROG --> CAN : cancel() — declared on the entity,<br/>no caller on current main

    DONE --> [*]
    FAIL --> [*]
    EXP --> [*]

    note right of PEN
        10 registered step handlers:
        DOCUMENT_SCAN, DATA_EXTRACT,
        FACE_MATCH, LIVENESS_CHECK,
        NFC_CHIP_READ, ADDRESS_PROOF,
        WATCHLIST_CHECK, AGE_VERIFICATION,
        PHONE_VERIFICATION, VIDEO_INTERVIEW.
    end note

    note right of CAN
        Terminal session states answer any
        further submission with HTTP 409.
        Manual review exists at STEP level
        (PENDING_REVIEW), not as a session
        state — the admin decision feeds the
        normal COMPLETED/FAILED outcome.
    end note

    class DONE okState
    class FAIL offState
    class EXP offState
    class CAN declState
    class SC okState
    class SF offState
